{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/point-your-camera-at-things-to-hear-how-to-say-them-in-another-language-fa6e9f3621a5", "time": 1683007076.7692, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/point-your-camera-at-things-to-hear-how-to-say-them-in-another-language-fa6e9f3621a5/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Point your camera at things to hear how to say them in another language | by Benson Ruan | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Point your camera at things to hear how to say them in another language", "description": "With Google Vision API and Translate API, Thing Translator web app lets you point your phone or laptop at stuff and hear to say it in a different language."}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://aiexperiments.withgoogle.com/", "anchor_text": "AI Experiments", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://cloud.google.com/vision/", "anchor_text": "Cloud Vision", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://cloud.google.com/translate/", "anchor_text": "Translate", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://cloud.google.com/apis/docs/getting-started", "anchor_text": "Google Cloud API getting started", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://github.com/dmotz/thing-translator", "anchor_text": "Thing Translator", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://github.com/bensonruan/", "anchor_text": "GitHub", "paragraph_index": 26}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/benson-ruan/", "anchor_text": "Linkedin", "paragraph_index": 26}], "all_paragraphs": ["When you travel to countries where you don\u2019t speak their language, Google Translate has become an invaluable tool. In most cases, you will speak to the app or type in the word to get the translation. Nowadays, with the camera feature in Google Translate, it allows you to essentially point your camera at text written in another language and then get a translation into your native one.", "When I was wondering whether I can bring such camera translate feature to the web, I came across this web app \u201cThing Translator\u201d. It was developed as part of Google\u2019s AI Experiments project, it lets you point your phone (or laptop) at stuff and hear to say it in a different language.", "Try it yourself in the link below:", "Behind the scenes, Thing Translator is using Google\u2019s Cloud Vision and Translate APIs. In this article, I will explore further into the code, please follow me so that you can also build this cool app yourself.", "Because this web app is using Google\u2019s Cloud API, to get started, you need to set up a project in Google to enable using 2 of its API.", "You might be afraid of Google would charge you for this experiment, please don\u2019t worry, you would be free of charge for experiment:", "Google provided a step by step instruction of how to set this up, more details can be found in Google Cloud API getting started", "Once you set up the API in GCP (Google Cloud Platform), copy and save the API Key to be used in the web app.", "Next, clone or download the Thing Translator repository from GitHub", "You will need to set your API key in src/config.js", "To start a development server on 9966 that will watch for code changes simply run:", "To optimize the output for production, run:", "Now, you can have fun playing with this camera translation web app, learn how to say some things in another language.", "If you are also curious about how it works behind the scenes, please follow me below to dive into the code.", "By using the Google Cloud Vision API, we want to pass the snapshot image, and get a response of what are the objects in the image.", "In src/effects/snap.js, you can find the code to call the Google Cloud Vision API in the snap function. The Vision API can perform LABEL_DETECTION on an image file by sending the contents of the image file as a base64 encoded string in the body of your request.", "If the request is successful, the server returns a 200 OK HTTP status code and the response in JSON format. A LABEL_DETECTION response includes the detected labels, their score, topicality, and an opaque label ID:", "Now, it gets half of the job done by detecting what is in the snapshot. Next, it will translate it into another language.", "By using the Google Cloud Translate API, we want to pass the word in English, and get a return of what\u2019s the translation in another language.", "In src/effects/translate.js, you can find the code to call the Google Cloud Translate API in the translate function. Below are the query parameters that we pass:", "If successful, the response body contains data with the following structure:", "Once it gets the translation back in the text, the last step is to know how to pronounce the word in the selected language.", "It utilize the browser\u2019s Speech Synthesis API to convert text to speech and speak out the translation.", "Speech Synthesis API converts normal language text into artificial speech, it is now supported by most of the modern browsers", "You can download the complete code of the above demo in the link below:", "This is one example of what you can make using Google\u2019s machine learning API\u2019s, without needing to dive into the details of machine learning. Without doubt, Google is one of the leading global companies that advanced in the fields of Machine Learning and AI. By standing on the shoulders of giants, you can see further into the future.", "Thank you for reading. If you like this article, please share on Facebook or Twitter. Let me know in the comment if you have any questions. Follow me on GitHub and Linkedin.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Diving into the world of Machine Learning and AI. Turning imagination into reality."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Ffa6e9f3621a5&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url"